# Project: squid

`squid` is an ergonomic Rust wrapper over [Poulpy](https://github.com/phantomzone-org/poulpy), a low-level, modular FHE toolkit. Poulpy exposes the full machinery of lattice-based homomorphic encryption and leaves resource management entirely to the caller. squid wraps it with a smaller, opinionated API.

## Current scope

squid currently wraps `poulpy-schemes::bin_fhe::bdd_arithmetic` only — the one fully exposed end-to-end capability in `poulpy-schemes`. That means:

- Key generation: `GLWESecret`, `LWESecret`, `BDDKey`
- Encrypt / decrypt `u8`, `u16`, `u32` via `FheUint`
- Homomorphic operations: `add`, `sub`, `xor`, `or`, `and`, `sll`, `srl`, `sra`, `slt`, `sltu`
- Scratch management across all of the above
- Lifecycle transitions: Standard -> Prepared for keys and ciphertexts

The scope will expand as `poulpy-schemes` adds more scheme-level implementations (CKKS, BGV, etc.).

## Public API surface

Everything flows through `Context`. The user-facing types are:

| Type | Role |
|---|---|
| `Context` | Owns `Module<BE>`, scratch arena, and `Params`. Entry point for all operations. |
| `Params` | Layout parameter bundle. Use `Params::default_128bit()` or construct custom. |
| `SecretKey` | Private key material: standard GLWE + LWE secrets and prepared GLWE for encrypt/decrypt. Returned by `Context::keygen`. |
| `EvaluationKey` | Public evaluation key bundle (`BDDKey` standard + prepared). Returned by `Context::keygen`. |
| `Ciphertext<T>` | Encrypted `T` value (`u8`, `u16`, `u32`). All ops run through `Context`. |
